Section 70, Record of government debt and finance arrangements of the Public Financial Management Act, 2016 mandates the The Public Debt Management Office to :

keep in a timely manner and in an appropriate database, comprehensive and accurate records of
(a) outstanding government debts;
(b) derivative transactions entered into by Government;
(c) guarantees issued by Government;
(d) government lending transactions;
(e) finance lease agreements entered into by Government; and
(f) any other relevant record in respect to Government debt
